Minimize Button:

	Use the Minimize button to change the visual representation
	of the base window at the pointer location to an icon. When
	an application base window is minimized, its associated
	transient (pop-up) windows are also unmapped.

To Minimize, click SELECT:

	To minimize a window containing a minimize button, move the
	mouse pointer into the area enclosed by the minimize button,
	and click SELECT while the pointer is inside this area. The
	window, it's associated transient windows, and all windows
	in the same window group as the window will be unmapped.
	The icon representing the minimized application will appear
	at the next available position on the screen according to
	the icon positioning resource.

